The death toll from the powerful earthquake in Turkey has risen to 7,085, with 33,559 injured, the government crisis center said early Friday, two days after the quake hit the northwestern part of the country.
In Izmit region, where the epicenter situated, 3,261 people were killed and 11,759 injured.
The earthquake, measuring 7.4 on the open-ended Richter scale, hit Turkey at 3:02 a.m. (0002 GMT) on Tuesday and lasted some 45 seconds when people were sleeping in bed.